WEBVTT

00:01.523 --> 00:05.048
- We are really going to shake
things up around here yet.

00:05.092 --> 00:06.310
- I could help you run lines.

00:06.354 --> 00:08.051
- Yeah, you know what?
Let's do it.

00:08.095 --> 00:09.835
- Are you nervous
about the kiss?

00:09.879 --> 00:11.315
- Pfft.
- I can show you.

00:11.359 --> 00:13.100
- While my prayers'
effect I take.

00:15.450 --> 00:17.060
[explosion and screaming]

00:17.104 --> 00:19.845
- Richie, we thought we
were going to die in there.

00:19.889 --> 00:22.065
- Yeah?
Did Buddy hold you real close?

00:22.109 --> 00:23.675
'Cause this is all about you

00:23.719 --> 00:26.765
and this dopey election that
you've roped everyone into,

00:26.809 --> 00:28.941
pretending it's all
for the greater good.

00:28.985 --> 00:30.682
But it's all about you!

00:30.726 --> 00:32.728
- It looks like
we're living through history.

00:32.771 --> 00:36.819
Rydell High has its
first female president.

00:36.862 --> 00:38.734
- You need to count
the ballots again.

00:38.777 --> 00:44.087
- You won because people
are inspired by you.

00:44.131 --> 00:46.220
I'm inspired by you.

00:46.263 --> 00:49.397
[soft dramatic music]

00:53.444 --> 00:56.447
[The Penguins' "Earth Angel"]

00:56.491 --> 00:59.059
- ♪ [harmonized vocalizing]

00:59.102 --> 01:03.193
- ♪ Earth angel, Earth angel

01:03.237 --> 01:07.893
- I can't stop thinking
about kissing you.

01:07.937 --> 01:10.635
- That's actually why I called.

01:10.679 --> 01:12.898
- Oh?

01:12.942 --> 01:15.510
That doesn't sound good.

01:15.553 --> 01:20.080
- I think we should keep
what happened between us.

01:20.123 --> 01:21.472
For now.
- Oh.

01:21.515 --> 01:24.084
- ♪ Earth angel, Earth angel

01:24.127 --> 01:25.737
- Okay.

01:25.781 --> 01:27.043
- It's just that--[sighs]

01:27.087 --> 01:28.958
I only recently
broke things off with Richie,

01:29.001 --> 01:31.787
and it can get--
- And you'd rather be with him.

01:31.830 --> 01:33.005
- No.

01:33.049 --> 01:36.747
[sighs] I don't know. I--

01:36.792 --> 01:40.143
you and I have
a lot to sort out.

01:40.187 --> 01:42.319
So much has happened, and--

01:42.363 --> 01:46.062
- And--and we don't have
to decide anything now.

01:46.106 --> 01:48.543
- Right.

01:48.586 --> 01:49.718
Thank you.

01:49.761 --> 01:51.241
- And besides,

01:51.285 --> 01:52.372
you are gonna have so much
on your plate as president.

01:52.416 --> 01:53.591
Trust me.

01:53.634 --> 01:55.158
- Maybe you can
show me the ropes.

01:55.202 --> 01:58.205
I would love your help.

01:58.247 --> 02:01.121
- Of course. Yeah.
[chuckles]

02:01.164 --> 02:02.687
We make a great team.

02:02.731 --> 02:05.821
- Yeah.

02:05.864 --> 02:06.865
It's getting late.

02:06.909 --> 02:08.911
- Good night.

02:08.954 --> 02:10.739
Madam President.

02:10.782 --> 02:12.654
- ♪ With you
- ♪ You

02:12.697 --> 02:13.742
- ♪ You
- ♪ You

02:13.785 --> 02:15.961
- [sighs heavily]

02:16.005 --> 02:17.572
- [sighs happily and giggles]

02:17.615 --> 02:18.834
[Jimmy Liggins'
"I Ain't Drunk"]

02:18.877 --> 02:21.837
- Then window,
let day in and let life out.

02:21.880 --> 02:25.362
- Farewell, farewell.
One kiss, and I'll descend.

02:25.406 --> 02:28.496
♪

02:28.539 --> 02:30.889
- ♪ One more round
won't get me down ♪

02:30.933 --> 02:32.761
- Give me my sin again,

02:32.804 --> 02:34.893
while my prayer's effect
I take.

02:34.937 --> 02:36.025
- ♪ We're drunk

02:36.067 --> 02:37.026
- Farewell.

02:37.069 --> 02:38.506
And I'll--[yelps]

02:38.549 --> 02:41.161
- ♪ Set 'em up,
another round ♪

02:41.944 --> 02:43.293
- Yeah, I put a lot of cheese
in there.

02:43.337 --> 02:45.382
Is that okay?
- It's okay. No, it's fine.

02:45.426 --> 02:46.383
[rowdy rock and roll music]

02:46.427 --> 02:47.906
- ♪ I ain't drunk

02:47.950 --> 02:50.257
♪ I'm just drinking,
that's all ♪

02:50.300 --> 02:53.085
♪

02:53.129 --> 02:54.391
- Good.

02:54.435 --> 02:58.047
I think that's it for today.

02:58.090 --> 02:59.656
- [clears throat]

03:01.703 --> 03:04.271
[sighs] Only two more days
of this, huh?

03:04.314 --> 03:06.577
- Yeah.
That's kinda how it works.

03:08.013 --> 03:10.015
I forget that this is your
first time doing a play,

03:10.059 --> 03:12.540
so I'll break it down for you.

03:12.583 --> 03:14.106
It's your whole life.

03:14.150 --> 03:15.934
It completely consumes you.

03:15.978 --> 03:17.197
And then one day, it's time.

03:17.240 --> 03:19.199
The curtain goes up,
you pour your heart out,

03:19.242 --> 03:20.896
it goes by far too fast,

03:20.939 --> 03:26.031
and then applause, applause,
curtain goes down, and boom.

03:26.075 --> 03:28.338
- Boom?

03:28.382 --> 03:31.907
- It's all over,
and we all move on.

03:34.866 --> 03:36.520
See you tomorrow.

03:36.564 --> 03:39.262
- Yeah.
[door opening and closing]

03:39.305 --> 03:43.223
- Oh, speak again,
bright angel,

03:43.266 --> 03:45.921
for thou art as glorious
to this night.

03:45.964 --> 03:49.968
Uh...uh...being--

03:51.796 --> 03:53.320
Okay, tell me.

03:53.363 --> 03:56.975
- Being o'er my head as is
a winged messenger of heaven.

03:57.019 --> 03:59.456
- I sure wish this Shakespeare
guy wrote in English.

03:59.500 --> 04:01.241
- Everybody makes that joke.

04:01.284 --> 04:03.199
Keep going.
- All right.

04:03.243 --> 04:06.898
Um, as is winged messenger
of heaven

04:06.942 --> 04:10.989
unto...

04:11.033 --> 04:13.340
- Unto the white-upturned
wond'ring eyes of mortals

04:13.383 --> 04:15.733
that fall back to gaze on him.

04:15.777 --> 04:17.300
- Jeez, Hazel.
- [chuckles]

04:17.344 --> 04:18.779
- I know you get stage fright,

04:18.822 --> 04:20.695
but it is bananas
that you are doing props

04:20.738 --> 04:22.262
when you have this whole play
memorized.

04:22.305 --> 04:23.567
If I asked Mr. Vaughan,

04:23.611 --> 04:24.655
I'm sure he could
find something for you.

04:24.699 --> 04:26.309
- Don't.

04:26.353 --> 04:28.311
I'm happy backstage.
I promise.

04:28.355 --> 04:30.095
- Mm, okay.

04:30.139 --> 04:31.749
[crickets chirping]

04:31.793 --> 04:34.970
- Hazel, I don't like
you out here on the roof.

04:35.013 --> 04:36.276
It's not safe.

04:36.319 --> 04:38.756
- But I used to do it
all the time back home.

04:38.800 --> 04:42.064
- The roof here is different.

04:42.107 --> 04:43.152
Good night, Buddy.

04:43.195 --> 04:44.893
- Good night, Mr. Robertson.

04:48.200 --> 04:50.899
[soft dramatic music]

04:50.942 --> 04:52.770
- You're spending
an awful lot of time

04:52.814 --> 04:55.033
rehearsing for a play
you're not in.

04:55.077 --> 04:57.034
- I'm just helping Buddy.

04:57.079 --> 04:59.516
I like helping.
That's why I like props.

04:59.560 --> 05:02.040
- What about this for the play?

05:02.084 --> 05:05.653
- Mom, I'm backstage.
It doesn't matter what I wear.

05:05.696 --> 05:07.959
- Not everyone needs
to be seen all the time.

05:08.003 --> 05:10.440
- Well, it's just hard when
you give birth to a star,

05:10.484 --> 05:13.269
and she's always
hiding her shine with...

05:13.313 --> 05:14.792
plaids.

05:14.836 --> 05:16.185
- There's nothing wrong
with plaid.

05:16.228 --> 05:18.361
- [gasps]
- I agree. Very sensible.

05:18.405 --> 05:21.016
- I give up with you two.

05:21.059 --> 05:23.366
- Maybe you should just
let her be.

05:23.410 --> 05:24.672
- I'm letting her be

05:24.715 --> 05:26.021
the beautiful young woman
that she is.

05:26.064 --> 05:28.066
She dresses like a lumberjack,
Lawrence.

05:28.110 --> 05:29.111
- [huffs softly]

05:29.154 --> 05:31.548
[energetic rock music]

05:31.592 --> 05:34.421
[engine revving
and tires squealing]

05:34.464 --> 05:41.645
♪

05:44.169 --> 05:46.737
[engine chugging]

05:46.781 --> 05:49.349
[upbeat rock music]

05:49.392 --> 05:52.221
♪

05:52.264 --> 05:53.701
- [gasps] Oh.

05:53.744 --> 05:58.401
♪ I know a secret
about one of you ♪

05:58.445 --> 06:00.621
- It's not me.
I am an open book.

06:00.664 --> 06:02.144
- You all have seen
my list of enemies.

06:02.187 --> 06:06.061
- Yes, and the crossed out
names are very unsettling.

06:06.104 --> 06:07.149
Jane won the election!

06:07.192 --> 06:08.455
- What?
- Yes!

06:08.498 --> 06:09.673
- Really?

06:09.717 --> 06:10.631
- I tried to call you
last night,

06:10.674 --> 06:11.980
but the line was busy.

06:12.023 --> 06:15.505
We did it. [sighs]
It was close, but we did it.

06:15.549 --> 06:17.202
- [sighs]
Thank Balenciaga.

06:17.246 --> 06:18.943
Now we can stop
worrying about the election

06:18.987 --> 06:21.424
and focus on the costumes
for the play.

06:21.468 --> 06:23.426
- Oh, right!
The play!

06:23.470 --> 06:26.777
Cynthia, are you ready
for your debut?

06:26.821 --> 06:29.345
[soft dramatic music]

06:29.389 --> 06:31.434
- Earth to Cynthia.
You okay?

06:31.478 --> 06:32.914
You seem off.
- You nervous?

06:32.957 --> 06:34.698
You want to talk about it?
- We're good listeners.

06:34.742 --> 06:36.308
- I'm just okay,
but I will try.

06:36.352 --> 06:38.136
- Jiminy!

06:38.180 --> 06:40.443
I'm on the rag, okay?

06:40.487 --> 06:42.924
Happy?

06:42.967 --> 06:45.492
- I'll go see if she
needs a sanitary napkin.

06:45.534 --> 06:46.928
Or to punch someone.

06:46.971 --> 06:49.757
Lots of uncrossed names
on my list.

06:51.454 --> 06:52.803
[engine revving]

06:52.847 --> 06:53.848
- I'm surprised he showed up.
- Let's go, boys!

06:53.891 --> 06:56.284
- He's been in a state
since Halloween.

06:56.328 --> 06:57.721
- Is he okay?

06:57.765 --> 06:59.288
- No.
[inhales deeply]

06:59.331 --> 07:00.898
But I'm not getting
in the middle of this.

07:00.942 --> 07:02.770
[soft downbeat music]

07:02.813 --> 07:04.380
Come on.

07:04.424 --> 07:06.600
Let's go practice our surprise
faces for the announcement.

07:06.643 --> 07:08.819
[engine revving]

07:08.863 --> 07:10.995
[tires screeching]
- [laughs]

07:11.039 --> 07:13.084
[downbeat music]

07:14.129 --> 07:16.479
[basketballs thumping]

07:16.523 --> 07:19.134
- All right, boys!
New basketball day!

07:19.177 --> 07:22.485
Have at it!
[cheering and laughter]

07:22.529 --> 07:24.095
[whistle blows]
- Don't worry, ladies.

07:24.139 --> 07:26.794
You get all the boys'
old basketballs.

07:28.404 --> 07:31.320
[laughter]

07:31.363 --> 07:32.495
- Joke's on him.

07:32.539 --> 07:35.498
I can make a hat out of this.

07:35.542 --> 07:37.892
[chimes play]

07:37.935 --> 07:40.198
- Good morning,
boys and girls,

07:40.242 --> 07:41.504
and thank you all

07:41.548 --> 07:44.551
for playing a part
in the democratic process.

07:44.594 --> 07:47.379
The results are in.

07:47.423 --> 07:51.034
Congratulations to...

07:51.079 --> 07:54.299
[suspenseful orchestral music]

07:54.343 --> 07:58.042
♪

07:58.086 --> 07:59.435
Buddy Aldridge.

07:59.479 --> 08:01.742
[cheering]

08:01.785 --> 08:03.787
Our returning president.

08:03.831 --> 08:06.050
[cheering and laughter]

08:06.094 --> 08:08.313
- What the heck, Olivia?
I thought you said Jane won.

08:08.357 --> 08:11.142
- She did.
I was there.

08:11.186 --> 08:13.318
- Well, it was nice
knowing you all.

08:13.362 --> 08:14.624
- What?

08:14.668 --> 08:16.408
- Let's face it.

08:16.452 --> 08:18.541
We started this whole group
so Jane could win the election,

08:18.585 --> 08:20.804
and she just lost.

08:20.848 --> 08:22.632
It was beautiful
while it lasted.

08:22.676 --> 08:23.938
- Cynthia,
what are you talking about?

08:23.981 --> 08:25.896
We're still friends.
- Are we?

08:25.940 --> 08:27.942
Or are we just four gals
who came together

08:27.985 --> 08:30.727
for a common goal
that we failed to achieve?

08:30.771 --> 08:33.077
- The Pink Ladies
are still a gang, win or lose.

08:33.121 --> 08:34.078
Nothing's changed.

08:34.121 --> 08:35.515
- You did it, Buddy!

08:35.558 --> 08:37.038
- Sorry. Excuse me.

08:39.823 --> 08:40.736
- And so it begins.

08:40.780 --> 08:42.609
[whistle blows]

08:42.652 --> 08:45.568
[sparse downbeat music]

08:45.612 --> 08:50.573
♪

08:50.617 --> 08:53.576
[soft tense music]

08:53.620 --> 08:54.838
♪

08:54.882 --> 08:56.057
[school bell rings]

08:56.100 --> 08:57.406
- Buddy actually had the nerve

08:57.449 --> 08:58.363
to ask you to help him out?

08:58.407 --> 08:59.451
- Yes.

08:59.495 --> 09:00.583
And I couldn't exactly say no

09:00.627 --> 09:02.629
because I asked him
the same thing.

09:02.672 --> 09:04.892
- When did that happen?

09:04.935 --> 09:08.243
- A while ago, just something
I said in good sportsmanship.

09:08.286 --> 09:10.375
- I thought we were going
to rule the school together,

09:10.419 --> 09:11.855
the Pink Ladies.

09:11.899 --> 09:14.597
- We still could,
just in a different way.

09:14.641 --> 09:15.990
- [sighs]

09:16.033 --> 09:18.601
- Look, if all I have now
is Buddy's ear,

09:18.645 --> 09:20.472
then that's
what I have to work with.

09:20.516 --> 09:22.866
Maybe I can still accomplish
the things we set out to do.

09:22.910 --> 09:28.132
I--I have to face it.
I lost.

09:28.176 --> 09:31.658
I can't be a sore loser.

09:31.701 --> 09:34.051
- So let me be one for you.

09:34.095 --> 09:36.401
Okay, do whatever you have
to do with Buddy.

09:36.445 --> 09:38.578
Well, not whatever.

09:38.621 --> 09:39.622
[laughing]
Not that you would.

09:39.665 --> 09:42.712
[laughs]
And I'll do the rest.

09:42.756 --> 09:45.454
I'm not done being
your campaign manager yet.

09:45.497 --> 09:48.413
[soft energetic music]

09:48.457 --> 09:53.027
♪

09:53.070 --> 09:54.681
Mr. Daniels.

09:54.724 --> 09:56.073
- I'm just leaving, Olivia.

09:56.117 --> 09:57.335
If you need to speak with me,

09:57.379 --> 09:58.815
you can do it during
school hours tomorrow.

09:58.859 --> 09:59.990
- It's about the newspaper.
- Really?

10:00.034 --> 10:01.296
Because if this is
just an excuse to--

10:01.339 --> 10:03.603
- It's not.

10:04.255 --> 10:09.826
You've made it very clear that
you want beige Barb, not me.

10:09.870 --> 10:12.437
I get the picture, okay?

10:12.481 --> 10:14.483
- Okay.

10:14.526 --> 10:15.658
What is it?

10:15.702 --> 10:16.659
- I have a story
I want to investigate,

10:16.703 --> 10:18.269
a story for the paper.

10:18.313 --> 10:21.229
I was there when
the PTA counted the votes.

10:21.272 --> 10:22.447
Jane won.

10:22.491 --> 10:25.276
But today, miraculously,
Buddy's president?

10:25.320 --> 10:27.670
Something's fishy.

10:27.714 --> 10:29.150
- [sighs softly]

10:29.193 --> 10:31.674
- Look, I'm a student
coming to a teacher for help.

10:31.718 --> 10:32.849
That's it.

10:32.893 --> 10:34.590
- Do you have any proof?

10:34.634 --> 10:37.593
- Not yet,
but I want to find some.

10:37.637 --> 10:39.943
- [sighs]

10:39.987 --> 10:41.597
[soft energetic music]

10:41.641 --> 10:43.860
- Excuse me.

10:43.904 --> 10:46.341
- Oh, sorry.

10:46.384 --> 10:50.388
- Oh, thinks't thou
we shall ever meet again?

10:50.432 --> 10:52.347
- I--I doubt not.

10:52.390 --> 10:53.783
And all these woes

10:53.827 --> 10:55.437
shall serve us sweet discourse
in our time to come.

10:55.480 --> 10:58.527
both: Oh, God.
I have an ill-divining soul.

10:58.570 --> 11:00.834
- Excuse me!
- Whoa.

11:00.877 --> 11:02.618
- Move.
- Oh.

11:02.662 --> 11:04.925
- Hazel, you okay?

11:04.968 --> 11:07.492
- Sorry.
- [chuckles] For what?

11:07.536 --> 11:08.972
- Um--

11:09.016 --> 11:11.105
- Hey, do you know where
I can buy a ticket to the play?

11:11.148 --> 11:14.151
- Yes, I've got them.
50¢.

11:18.373 --> 11:20.157
You coming to see Buddy?

11:20.201 --> 11:22.856
- Uh, not really.

11:25.162 --> 11:26.686
- Adieu!

11:26.729 --> 11:28.252
Adieu.

11:28.296 --> 11:30.907
- Hold!

11:30.951 --> 11:32.561
You were awful.

11:32.604 --> 11:36.434
I've seen more passion from
the sales girl at Smith & Lang.

11:36.478 --> 11:39.699
Lydia!

11:39.742 --> 11:40.917
Double up your
rehearsal time with her.

11:40.961 --> 11:42.353
- I really think I got it,
Mr. B.

11:42.397 --> 11:43.964
- You are incorrect.

11:44.007 --> 11:46.053
Don't go easy on her.

11:46.096 --> 11:48.969
Tears are essential for growth.

11:49.012 --> 11:52.624
Time for my treat--

11:52.668 --> 11:53.625
costumes!

11:53.669 --> 11:54.844
Mm!

11:54.888 --> 11:56.367
[quirky downbeat note]

11:56.411 --> 11:58.587
- I still need to put a
few finishing touches and--

11:58.630 --> 12:00.067
- Yes, for example,

12:00.110 --> 12:02.765
I think Romeo
should wear pants.

12:02.809 --> 12:04.898
Where are
all the other costumes?

12:04.941 --> 12:08.771
- I'm working on
Juliet's dress right now.

12:08.815 --> 12:12.383
- And the rest of Verona?

12:12.427 --> 12:15.125
Are you aware
we open tomorrow night?

12:15.169 --> 12:17.737
How are we to have
a dress rehearsal

12:17.780 --> 12:19.521
if no one is dressed?

12:19.564 --> 12:22.176
- Art takes time.

12:22.219 --> 12:25.570
- The curtain waits for no one.

12:25.614 --> 12:27.529
You have exactly...

12:27.572 --> 12:29.574
26 hours to finish your "art."

12:29.618 --> 12:31.751
You all will help her.

12:31.794 --> 12:35.319
Where is "Hazelle?"
She's always standing around.

12:35.363 --> 12:36.190
- I'm right here.

12:36.233 --> 12:37.974
- Ah.
- I work alone!

12:38.018 --> 12:39.715
- Not anymore.

12:39.759 --> 12:41.717
These actors need costumes.

12:41.761 --> 12:45.765
They can't very well
go on stage nude, can they?

12:45.808 --> 12:47.984
Can they?

12:48.028 --> 12:51.553
No.
We need costumes.

12:51.596 --> 12:52.554
Please.

12:52.597 --> 12:54.817
[claps] Please.

12:54.861 --> 12:56.384
[sighs]

13:01.128 --> 13:03.478
[soft energetic music]

13:03.521 --> 13:04.740
- [inhales deeply]

13:04.784 --> 13:05.872
Pants.

13:14.750 --> 13:17.622
[Bing Crosby's
"Quizas, Quizas, Quizas"]

13:17.666 --> 13:18.972
- Oh.

13:19.015 --> 13:20.930
This is...

13:20.974 --> 13:23.759
quite the mood to discuss
student council policy.

13:23.803 --> 13:25.892
- Yeah,
we're talking about dance.

13:25.935 --> 13:27.458
I figure we could
use some music.

13:27.502 --> 13:29.634
- ♪ Why do her eyes say,
"Quizás, quizás, quizás"? ♪

13:29.678 --> 13:30.940
- Can't blame a guy for trying.

13:30.984 --> 13:33.682
[both chuckle]

13:33.725 --> 13:34.944
- Oh.

13:34.988 --> 13:36.598
They gave you the
president's gavel.

13:36.641 --> 13:39.340
- Yeah. Well, I still
had it from last year.

13:39.383 --> 13:41.777
- Right.

13:41.821 --> 13:43.300
- You can hold it.
- No.

13:43.344 --> 13:44.388
That's okay.

13:44.432 --> 13:48.262
- ♪ Quizás, quizás, quizás

13:48.305 --> 13:51.743
- ♪ Hello-oh, Mr. President

13:51.787 --> 13:53.702
Ooh, it's dark.

13:53.745 --> 13:58.272
- Susan, I--oh.

13:58.315 --> 13:59.882
- What is she doing here?

13:59.926 --> 14:03.146
- Jane has agreed to help me
with a few presidential duties.

14:03.190 --> 14:05.757
[chuckles]
What are you doing here?

14:05.801 --> 14:08.456
- Well, considering
I just spent the last month

14:08.499 --> 14:10.893
managing your campaign,
which you won,

14:10.937 --> 14:14.288
I assumed
we'd continue to work together.

14:14.331 --> 14:16.029
So sorry for your loss,
by the way.

14:16.072 --> 14:17.552
It must have been brutal
getting so close

14:17.595 --> 14:18.901
and still losing.

14:18.945 --> 14:20.555
- Thanks, Susan.

14:20.598 --> 14:23.079
- I'm sure we can all figure
out a way to work together.

14:23.123 --> 14:24.820
- No.
- Absolutely not.

14:24.864 --> 14:26.778
- You have to choose.
- Her or me.

14:26.822 --> 14:28.084
- Come on.
We don't have to choose.

14:28.128 --> 14:29.477
together: Yes!

14:29.520 --> 14:32.741
♪

14:32.784 --> 14:35.091
- I--I choose Jane.

14:35.135 --> 14:36.397
I'm sorry, Susan.

14:36.440 --> 14:39.966
- You have some nerve,
Buddy Aldridge.

14:40.009 --> 14:43.578
♪

14:43.621 --> 14:45.928
[Susan screaming]

14:45.972 --> 14:47.799
[door slams]

14:47.843 --> 14:50.585
- ♪ Quizás, quizás, quizás
- ♪ Quizás, quizás, quizás

14:50.628 --> 14:52.065
♪

14:52.108 --> 14:53.066
- ♪ Could be

14:53.109 --> 14:54.937
[gavel taps]

14:54.981 --> 14:56.112
- You have the floor.

14:56.156 --> 14:59.115
[quirky music]

14:59.159 --> 15:06.209
♪

15:10.300 --> 15:13.521
- Nancy, what are you doing?

15:13.564 --> 15:14.739
- Working.

15:14.783 --> 15:19.266
- So from
a time management perspective,

15:19.309 --> 15:22.660
we need to do 12 costumes
in 23 hours.

15:22.704 --> 15:24.140
Maybe if you could
simplify your designs

15:24.184 --> 15:25.925
and delegate some sewing--

15:29.972 --> 15:32.583
- I'll delegate
when I can clone myself.

15:32.627 --> 15:36.544
You like science.
Maybe go get a jump on that.

15:36.587 --> 15:38.633
- Nancy,
I'm trying to help you,

15:38.676 --> 15:40.504
and you're being
completely unreasonable.

15:40.548 --> 15:43.681
- I don't need your help
compromising my vision,

15:43.725 --> 15:45.553
so just do me a favor

15:45.596 --> 15:49.296
and go back to fading
into the wallpaper backstage.

15:49.339 --> 15:50.906
- I don't fade
into the wallpaper.

15:50.950 --> 15:52.429
- Oh, this isn't you?

15:52.473 --> 15:54.692
[gasps] Oh, excuse me.
[giggles]

15:54.736 --> 15:56.651
Oh! My apologies.

15:56.694 --> 15:58.827
Sorry for existing.

15:58.870 --> 16:00.089
[nasally] I'm Hazel.

16:00.133 --> 16:03.527
♪

16:03.571 --> 16:06.008
- Well, this is you.

16:06.052 --> 16:08.358
Out of my way!
I'm Nancy!

16:08.402 --> 16:10.273
I have vision, I swear!

16:10.317 --> 16:13.929
Even though I can't make--
oh, oh, a single decision!

16:13.973 --> 16:18.934
♪

16:18.978 --> 16:20.327
- [nasally] I'm Hazel.

16:20.370 --> 16:22.285
I'm just reminding you
that I'm here

16:22.329 --> 16:25.462
because I'm so forgettable.

16:25.506 --> 16:28.335
all: Oh.

16:28.378 --> 16:31.512
[suspenseful music]

16:31.555 --> 16:34.950
♪

16:34.994 --> 16:36.778
- Good luck, Nancy.

16:36.821 --> 16:37.909
Since you're such a genius,

16:37.953 --> 16:40.695
I'm sure you can do this
all alone.

16:40.738 --> 16:44.090
[downbeat music]

16:44.133 --> 16:46.831
- Does that mean we can go too?

16:46.875 --> 16:48.137
- Please!

16:48.181 --> 16:49.530
♪

16:49.573 --> 16:51.227
- [stifled laugh]
[indistinct chatter]

16:51.271 --> 16:58.539
♪

16:58.930 --> 17:00.541
- How now!
Who calls?

17:00.584 --> 17:03.674
- Your mother.
- Madam, I am here.

17:03.718 --> 17:05.111
- Okay.
[scoffs]

17:05.154 --> 17:07.548
- What are we doing?

17:07.590 --> 17:10.507
- Rehearsing.

17:10.550 --> 17:11.900
- Why?

17:11.943 --> 17:13.423
- Because we open tomorrow.

17:13.467 --> 17:15.772
- I know, but what's the point?

17:15.817 --> 17:17.210
It's like you said.

17:17.252 --> 17:19.080
Everyone gets all worked up
for weeks, and then--

17:19.125 --> 17:23.172
and then it's 90 minutes
of thous and wherefores.

17:23.215 --> 17:26.480
And then after that,
it's--it's all a wash.

17:26.522 --> 17:29.526
- That's not
exactly what I said.

17:29.570 --> 17:32.703
It may only be 90 minutes,
but for those 90 minutes, you--

17:32.747 --> 17:35.141
- Spare me.

17:35.184 --> 17:36.707
Thanks for your help.

17:36.751 --> 17:39.101
[clears throat]
I know all the words.

17:39.145 --> 17:40.798
I'll be fine.

17:42.974 --> 17:45.629
Unless...

17:45.673 --> 17:49.111
there's something else
you wanted to say.

17:49.155 --> 17:52.288
[soft dramatic music]

17:52.332 --> 17:54.856
♪

17:54.899 --> 17:57.032
- You need to enunciate more.

17:57.076 --> 17:58.773
You swallow your consonants.

18:04.126 --> 18:06.085
[The Rockettes' "Love Nobody"]

18:06.128 --> 18:09.088
[all shouting]

18:09.131 --> 18:13.440
- ♪ Ain't gonna love nobody
till somebody loves me ♪

18:13.483 --> 18:16.486
- Susan! Susan!
Over here!

18:16.530 --> 18:17.966
Whoo-hoo!

18:18.009 --> 18:21.317
- ♪ 'Cause the last man
I loved made a fool of me ♪

18:21.361 --> 18:23.580
- ♪ [harmonized vocalizing]

18:23.624 --> 18:25.930
- ♪ I ain't gonna
love nobody ♪

18:25.974 --> 18:27.323
- Mom.

18:27.367 --> 18:29.369
♪

18:29.412 --> 18:31.284
- Why the long face?

18:31.327 --> 18:33.199
Is it that time of the month?
You look puffy.

18:33.242 --> 18:35.592
- What are you doing here?
- PTA meeting.

18:35.636 --> 18:38.160
Now, spill.
I can tell something's wrong.

18:38.204 --> 18:41.163
[indistinct chatter]

18:41.207 --> 18:43.165
♪

18:43.209 --> 18:44.471
- I won Buddy the
whole election,

18:44.514 --> 18:47.082
and he ditched me
for Jane Facciano again.

18:47.126 --> 18:48.736
- Oh, bumblebee.

18:48.779 --> 18:51.347
I always tell you
you're too eager with the boys.

18:51.391 --> 18:52.696
They don't like it.

18:52.740 --> 18:54.872
They like to feel like
they're on the chase.

18:54.916 --> 18:57.745
It's very primal.

18:57.788 --> 18:59.834
Is that baloney?

18:59.877 --> 19:01.052
- [laughing]
Mother, I'm hungry.

19:01.096 --> 19:02.097
I haven't eaten all day,

19:02.141 --> 19:04.360
and I have to go
to driver's ed.

19:04.404 --> 19:06.797
- You're not hungry,
you're upset.

19:06.841 --> 19:08.059
And for no reason.

19:08.103 --> 19:11.280
That girl isn't half
as pretty as you.

19:11.324 --> 19:13.326
You'll get him back.

19:13.369 --> 19:16.067
These always add
a pep to my step.

19:16.111 --> 19:19.767
And you need to keep up with
them if you want to stay trim.

19:19.810 --> 19:21.986
Better take two.

19:22.030 --> 19:27.383
♪

19:27.427 --> 19:29.733
[school bell rings]

19:30.865 --> 19:33.781
[indistinct chatter]

19:38.307 --> 19:40.962
- Oh, perfect.

19:41.005 --> 19:42.529
- Mm.

19:42.572 --> 19:44.183
- Oh, good, two girls.

19:44.226 --> 19:45.445
Who wants to go first?

19:45.488 --> 19:46.446
- Me.
- I'll go.

19:46.489 --> 19:48.230
[energetic music]

19:48.274 --> 19:49.318
- [chuckling]
Oh, good.

19:49.362 --> 19:51.364
Two girls
who don't like each other.

19:51.407 --> 19:54.454
♪

19:54.497 --> 19:57.021
Keep your hands
at 10:00 and 2:00

19:57.065 --> 19:58.762
and your claws retracted.

19:58.806 --> 20:05.291
♪

20:05.334 --> 20:06.814
Antacid, anyone?

20:06.857 --> 20:08.250
- All right,

20:08.294 --> 20:10.600
let's run through the lighting
for the kiss again.

20:10.644 --> 20:13.342
Romeo, Juliet, hither.

20:16.563 --> 20:18.391
- [exhales deeply]

20:19.914 --> 20:24.788
And I'll still stay
to have thee still forget,

20:24.832 --> 20:27.748
forgetting any other home
but this.

20:27.791 --> 20:30.446
- Romeo,
why do you have your sword?

20:30.490 --> 20:33.144
Are you planning on
wooing Juliet or stabbing her?

20:33.188 --> 20:36.278
- Whoops. Sorry.
- Yes.

20:36.322 --> 20:38.324
- I can take it.
- Oh, hi.

20:38.367 --> 20:39.977
I forgot you were here.
[laughs]

20:41.414 --> 20:45.069
- "Hazelle," clear the stage.
Focus, everyone.

20:45.113 --> 20:50.379
Four hours until curtain,
and then God help us all.

20:50.423 --> 20:51.989
All right.

20:52.033 --> 20:53.426
- And I'll still stay.

20:53.469 --> 20:55.079
[soft downbeat music]

20:55.123 --> 20:57.604
- See that?
213 people signed in to vote.

20:57.647 --> 21:01.564
But if you look here--
- Only 181 votes counted.

21:01.608 --> 21:03.871
That's a pretty big margin.
- I know.

21:03.914 --> 21:05.089
It can't be a mistake.

21:05.133 --> 21:06.134
- It's not conclusive.

21:06.177 --> 21:07.396
You still need more proof,

21:07.440 --> 21:08.963
but I think you might have
cracked this open.

21:09.006 --> 21:10.269
- And you're not going
to let the administration

21:10.312 --> 21:11.574
shut down the story?

21:11.618 --> 21:13.924
- Even teachers have
to feel alive sometimes.

21:13.968 --> 21:15.665
- That's so sad.

21:15.709 --> 21:16.840
- Hey.

21:16.884 --> 21:18.059
[both chuckle]

21:18.102 --> 21:19.408
- [inhales deeply]

21:19.452 --> 21:22.063
I was thinking--
everyone voted during homeroom.

21:22.106 --> 21:23.673
If we can get the specific
attendance records,

21:23.717 --> 21:25.414
then we can be sure
votes are missing.

21:29.375 --> 21:31.420
Okay.
- [clears throat]

21:31.464 --> 21:33.944
[suspenseful music]

21:33.988 --> 21:40.995
♪

21:41.212 --> 21:43.345
- If you can sneak those
records to my office tonight,

21:43.389 --> 21:45.086
we can go over them together.

21:45.129 --> 21:47.393
The school will be open
for the play.

21:47.436 --> 21:49.351
♪

21:49.395 --> 21:51.397
- Okay.

21:51.440 --> 21:54.269
8 o'clock?

21:54.313 --> 21:55.836
- Perfect.

21:55.879 --> 21:59.187
♪

21:59.230 --> 22:01.885
- [sighs]

22:01.929 --> 22:03.713
- What were you and
Mr. Daniels discussing?

22:03.757 --> 22:05.498
- A story
for "The Rydell Review."

22:05.541 --> 22:07.456
- You're still
in newspaper club?

22:07.500 --> 22:10.111
- Kind of.

22:10.154 --> 22:12.243
Miss McGee, you were there.

22:12.287 --> 22:13.375
Jane won.

22:13.419 --> 22:14.811
We both heard.

22:14.855 --> 22:16.552
- I know, dear,
but it was an error.

22:16.596 --> 22:19.642
I double checked it myself
after the PTA's recount.

22:19.686 --> 22:21.252
- Were you there
for the recount?

22:21.296 --> 22:24.560
- Well, no, but--

22:24.604 --> 22:26.954
Olivia,
if we can speak frankly--

22:26.997 --> 22:29.043
- I'd love to.

22:29.086 --> 22:32.960
I smell a rat in this election,
and I know you do too.

22:33.003 --> 22:35.528
But I guess I'm the only
one who cares enough

22:35.571 --> 22:37.486
to do something about it.

22:40.968 --> 22:43.405
- [sighs]

22:43.449 --> 22:45.276
[quirky music]

22:45.320 --> 22:48.410
- [slowly] Any day now.

22:48.454 --> 22:49.977
[engine chugging]

22:50.020 --> 22:52.414
[breaks squeal
and tires screech]

22:52.458 --> 22:54.242
[Jane sighs]

22:54.285 --> 22:55.504
[engine shuts off]

22:55.548 --> 22:57.158
♪

22:57.201 --> 22:59.465
And where do I catch
the shuttle to the curb?

22:59.508 --> 23:01.292
[Susan giggles]
- Sorry.

23:01.336 --> 23:03.251
- You, get in front.

23:03.294 --> 23:06.341
You're jumpy, but at least
we'll get home tonight.

23:06.385 --> 23:09.605
Oh, look.
We're at my dry cleaners.

23:09.649 --> 23:11.433
I'll be right back.

23:16.003 --> 23:17.221
both: I just--

23:17.265 --> 23:18.266
both: Can you--

23:18.309 --> 23:19.223
- Come on.
- [groans]

23:19.267 --> 23:20.877
[bicycle bell rings]

23:25.229 --> 23:27.971
[Susan clears throat]

23:28.015 --> 23:30.017
- Is he gonna make us run
errands for him all afternoon?

23:30.060 --> 23:31.845
- What, are you worried
about missing the play?

23:31.888 --> 23:33.194
Buddy would be so upset

23:33.237 --> 23:34.500
if he didn't see you drooling
in the audience.

23:34.543 --> 23:35.936
- Can we not talk about Buddy?

23:35.979 --> 23:37.198
- I honestly don't even know
what he sees in you.

23:37.241 --> 23:38.808
You're not even pretty.

23:38.852 --> 23:40.897
- Susan, if you were any
shallower, you'd be a puddle!

23:43.422 --> 23:46.033
- Okay, blondie.

23:46.076 --> 23:48.296
You know where
the post office is?

23:48.339 --> 23:50.037
- Yes.

23:50.080 --> 23:51.386
Right.

23:51.430 --> 23:53.736
[engine turns over]

23:53.780 --> 23:55.434
[emergency brake ratchets]

23:55.477 --> 23:57.131
[tires squeak]

23:57.174 --> 23:58.393
- Susan! Be careful.

23:58.437 --> 23:59.481
- I know what I'm doing!

23:59.525 --> 24:00.700
- Don't be hysterical, girls.

24:00.743 --> 24:02.136
- Shouldn't she
check her mirrors

24:02.179 --> 24:03.442
before pulling into traffic?
- Just shut it, Jane!

24:03.485 --> 24:05.574
It's my turn now.
[engine revving]

24:05.618 --> 24:08.055
[energetic rock music]

24:08.098 --> 24:09.404
[tires squealing]

24:09.448 --> 24:11.058
♪

24:11.101 --> 24:13.887
♪ Little girl
with the perfect smile ♪

24:13.930 --> 24:16.672
♪ Learned to talk, learned
to walk every extra mile ♪

24:16.716 --> 24:19.632
♪ Little girl with
the perfect painted skin ♪

24:19.675 --> 24:22.635
♪ Learned to just
only apologize again ♪

24:22.678 --> 24:25.202
♪ I never got a chance
to decide ♪

24:25.246 --> 24:28.075
♪ What I did, who I was,
it was idealized ♪

24:28.118 --> 24:30.860
♪ If I ever crossed
a dotted line ♪

24:30.904 --> 24:34.560
♪ It was shame, it was tamed,
and it was criticized ♪

24:34.603 --> 24:37.432
♪ I want to be big,
I want to be bold ♪

24:37.476 --> 24:40.130
♪ But I'm doing as I'm told

24:40.174 --> 24:43.003
♪ I want to be seen,
I want to be loud ♪

24:43.046 --> 24:45.309
♪ But they'll
never hear a sound ♪

24:45.353 --> 24:49.183
♪ How can I recognize
when it's my time ♪

24:49.226 --> 24:53.187
♪ When I was never allowed
to try? ♪

24:53.230 --> 24:57.539
♪ That's why
girls, girls can't drive ♪

24:57.583 --> 24:58.627
♪

24:58.671 --> 25:01.761
♪ Ooh, ooh-ooh

25:01.804 --> 25:03.284
♪ Girls can't drive

25:03.327 --> 25:08.071
♪

25:08.115 --> 25:10.596
♪ Since I've been
so powerless ♪

25:10.639 --> 25:13.686
♪ I backseat-drive,
manipulative ♪

25:13.729 --> 25:16.340
♪ Survival is
a learned lesson ♪

25:16.384 --> 25:20.127
♪ So I do what it takes to,
what it takes to win ♪

25:20.170 --> 25:22.869
♪ I want to be big,
I want to be bold ♪

25:22.912 --> 25:26.046
♪ But I'm doing as I'm told

25:26.089 --> 25:29.005
♪ I want to be seen,
I want to be loud ♪

25:29.049 --> 25:31.051
♪ But they'll never
hear a sound ♪

25:31.094 --> 25:35.185
♪ How can I recognize
when it's my time ♪

25:35.229 --> 25:39.015
♪ When I was never allowed
to try? ♪

25:39.059 --> 25:44.194
♪ That's why
girls, girls can't drive ♪

25:44.238 --> 25:46.936
♪ For so long

25:46.980 --> 25:49.852
♪ I've kept what

25:49.896 --> 25:55.336
♪ What I want deep in

25:55.379 --> 25:58.382
♪ So if I

25:58.426 --> 26:02.822
♪ Said it out loud

26:02.865 --> 26:05.433
♪ I wouldn't believe it

26:05.476 --> 26:07.653
[flames whoosh]
all: ♪ I'm going to be big

26:07.696 --> 26:08.871
♪ I'm going to be bold

26:08.915 --> 26:11.961
♪ I won't do as I am told

26:12.005 --> 26:14.964
♪ I'm going to be seen,
I'm going to be loud ♪

26:15.008 --> 26:17.184
♪ Until they hear every sound

26:17.227 --> 26:21.188
♪ How can I recognize
when it's my time ♪

26:21.231 --> 26:25.235
♪ When I was never allowed
to try? ♪

26:25.279 --> 26:32.286
♪ That's why
girls, girls can't drive ♪

26:32.329 --> 26:33.722
♪

26:33.766 --> 26:38.640
♪ Girls can't drive

26:38.684 --> 26:43.689
♪ Girls, girls can't drive

26:43.732 --> 26:44.994
♪

26:45.038 --> 26:49.912
♪ Girls can't drive

26:49.956 --> 26:51.958
♪ Girls, girls can't drive

26:52.001 --> 26:54.656
- Susan! Susan, slow down!
[engine revving]

26:54.700 --> 26:55.918
- What in the Sam Hill's
going on?

26:55.962 --> 26:58.268
- Stop yelling at me!
- Susan, please!

26:58.312 --> 26:59.835
- Pull over!
[Susan and Jane screaming]

26:59.879 --> 27:02.664
[tires squealing]
Brake, brake!

27:06.450 --> 27:08.191
[Susan whimpers]

27:10.759 --> 27:13.544
[steam hissing]

27:13.588 --> 27:16.591
[soft dramatic music]

27:16.635 --> 27:19.594
Everyone okay?

27:19.638 --> 27:20.726
Stay here.

27:20.769 --> 27:22.902
I'll be back with a tow truck.

27:22.945 --> 27:26.122
[ominous music]

27:26.166 --> 27:29.430
♪

27:35.479 --> 27:37.003
- Whew.
There we go.

27:37.046 --> 27:38.439
[snaps fingers and chuckles]

27:38.482 --> 27:39.832
[knock at door]
Yep?

27:39.875 --> 27:41.311
- May I have a word?

27:41.355 --> 27:42.661
- Okay, but just one.

27:42.704 --> 27:44.401
- [sighing chuckle]

27:44.445 --> 27:45.533
I--
- Oh!

27:45.576 --> 27:47.230
That's your one.
- [laughs exasperatedly]

27:47.274 --> 27:48.275
- [chuckles]

27:48.318 --> 27:49.363
- There have
been some questions

27:49.406 --> 27:51.452
about the vote count
of the election.

27:51.495 --> 27:54.977
I saw with my own eyes
that Jane Facciano won.

27:55.021 --> 27:57.240
- Maybe you should get
some new spectacles.

27:57.284 --> 28:00.896
- My prescription is up
to date, thank you very much.

28:04.639 --> 28:06.597
- She did,
but I gave it to Buddy.

28:06.641 --> 28:08.251
He needs it more.
For college.

28:08.295 --> 28:10.471
- What about Jane?
She earned it.

28:10.514 --> 28:12.429
And she wants to go to college.
- [scoffs]

28:12.473 --> 28:14.867
Girls just go to college
to get their MRS degree.

28:14.910 --> 28:16.912
Buddy could really
be someone in this world.

28:16.956 --> 28:18.609
- I went to college.

28:18.653 --> 28:20.089
- Really?
Hmm.

28:20.133 --> 28:21.743
I didn't.

28:21.787 --> 28:25.007
Look, being a principal is all
about making tough decisions.

28:25.051 --> 28:27.618
You'll find that out
when I, uh,

28:27.662 --> 28:29.229
name you as my replacement.

28:29.272 --> 28:33.015
- What?

28:33.059 --> 28:34.756
- I'm running
for superintendent.

28:34.800 --> 28:37.237
Shh, secret.

28:37.280 --> 28:39.761
And if I win
and you play your cards right,

28:39.805 --> 28:44.592
well, um,
all this could be yours.

28:44.635 --> 28:46.376
Except that.

28:46.420 --> 28:48.422
I'm taking that with me.

28:48.465 --> 28:50.250
So hands off.

28:50.293 --> 28:51.425
All right.

28:51.468 --> 28:52.469
[clears throat]

28:52.513 --> 28:55.429
[soft downbeat music]

28:55.472 --> 28:57.736
♪

28:57.779 --> 28:59.346
- [huffs]

28:59.389 --> 29:06.266
♪

29:13.490 --> 29:15.492
[softly] Perfection.

29:16.406 --> 29:19.322
[soft tense notes]

29:23.152 --> 29:24.980
[sighs]

29:25.024 --> 29:28.418
- I am hurt.
A plague o' both your houses!

29:28.462 --> 29:30.203
- Hazel.
- [gasps]

29:30.246 --> 29:31.030
- I'm sorry.

29:31.073 --> 29:32.814
For that and for before.

29:32.858 --> 29:34.903
[inhales deeply]

29:34.947 --> 29:38.428
You were r--
[takes deep breath]

29:38.472 --> 29:41.692
[slowly]
R-right.

29:41.736 --> 29:44.043
[inhales deeply]
And I need...

29:44.086 --> 29:46.393
[slowly]
Help.

29:46.436 --> 29:48.874
[takes deep breath]

29:50.266 --> 29:52.051
Unless you have something else
to do.

29:52.094 --> 29:53.661
[soft dramatic music]

29:53.704 --> 29:54.793
- I do.

29:54.836 --> 29:56.359
- Hmm.

29:56.403 --> 30:00.842
♪

30:00.886 --> 30:01.800
- Okay, I'm done.
Let's go.

30:01.843 --> 30:03.149
- Oh.

30:03.192 --> 30:06.152
[energetic suspenseful music]

30:06.195 --> 30:07.675
[Nancy sighs heavily]

30:07.718 --> 30:09.764
- Okay.

30:09.808 --> 30:11.897
- I know, I know.

30:11.940 --> 30:15.465
It's hopeless.

30:15.509 --> 30:17.337
Wait, Nancy,
what are you talking about?

30:17.380 --> 30:18.860
- [groans]
- These are incredible!

30:18.904 --> 30:20.819
- Those aren't costumes.

30:20.862 --> 30:22.995
They're just muslin prototypes.

30:23.038 --> 30:26.172
It's cheap fabric you use
to design patterns.

30:26.215 --> 30:27.869
These have been done for weeks.

30:27.913 --> 30:29.871
- These could be the costumes.

30:29.915 --> 30:31.264
- But everyone
would look the same.

30:31.307 --> 30:36.225
- Except Romeo and Juliet.

30:36.269 --> 30:38.445
- 'Cause they're in love.

30:38.488 --> 30:40.012
Allegedly.

30:40.055 --> 30:43.189
Seems like a pretty superficial
relationship to me, but...

30:43.232 --> 30:45.669
conceptually, this works.

30:45.713 --> 30:46.932
- It more than works.

30:46.975 --> 30:48.716
It's art that you made.

30:48.759 --> 30:50.631
- [squeals] Yeah.

30:50.674 --> 30:54.461
But the vision is bold,
and that's you.

30:54.504 --> 30:56.550
♪

31:00.946 --> 31:03.905
- Here you go.

31:04.906 --> 31:07.474
- Thanks.

31:11.304 --> 31:12.653
I'll bet you're going
to tell the whole school

31:12.696 --> 31:15.308
how I went crazy and
drove us off a cliff, right?

31:15.351 --> 31:17.876
- I wasn't planning on it.
- Of course.

31:17.919 --> 31:20.530
You're too good of a person.

31:20.574 --> 31:23.272
I wasn't being facetious.
You actually are a good person.

31:23.316 --> 31:25.971
That's why,
no matter how hard I try,

31:26.014 --> 31:28.799
Buddy is never going
to choose me over you.

31:28.843 --> 31:30.410
Not as a girlfriend.

31:30.453 --> 31:32.803
[sarcastically]
Not even for student council.

31:32.847 --> 31:36.242
- He may have chosen me,

31:36.285 --> 31:39.114
but I'm still just number two.

31:39.158 --> 31:41.769
I don't really have any power.
- Honestly...

31:41.812 --> 31:43.902
for someone so smart,
you're pretty stupid.

31:43.945 --> 31:45.338
- [gasps]

31:45.381 --> 31:47.731
- People at Rydell are gaga
over the Pink Ladies.

31:47.775 --> 31:50.082
They actually care
about what you have to say,

31:50.125 --> 31:52.040
and they listen
when you say it.

31:52.084 --> 31:55.000
That's power, stupid.

31:55.043 --> 31:56.958
- Wow.

31:57.002 --> 32:01.136
That was...actually insightful.

32:05.488 --> 32:06.707
- And I'm...

32:06.750 --> 32:09.188
[soft tense music]

32:09.231 --> 32:14.106
Sorry for
almost killing us earlier.

32:14.149 --> 32:15.324
But you're not a good driver,
either.

32:15.368 --> 32:16.673
- I know.

32:16.717 --> 32:18.110
I-it bothers me so much

32:18.153 --> 32:19.850
'cause it's such a stereotype,
you know?

32:19.894 --> 32:21.330
- Yeah.
[chuckles]

32:21.374 --> 32:23.376
[car door slams]
- Gas station's closed.

32:23.419 --> 32:26.727
We have to walk back.
- What?

32:26.770 --> 32:28.772
That's gotta be three miles.

32:28.816 --> 32:34.082
- Better get used to it
because you both flunked.

32:34.126 --> 32:35.475
- Flunked?

32:35.518 --> 32:39.348
Flunked?

32:39.392 --> 32:40.610
You--you don't understand.

32:40.654 --> 32:42.743
I've never flunked anything
in my life.

32:42.786 --> 32:44.136
Can we talk about this?

32:44.179 --> 32:46.573
My parents are not gonna
be happy to hear that.

32:46.616 --> 32:49.532
[downbeat music]

32:49.576 --> 32:51.186
♪

32:51.230 --> 32:54.233
- Wait for me!

32:54.276 --> 32:55.756
♪

32:55.799 --> 32:56.931
[suspenseful music]

32:56.975 --> 32:58.454
- What are you
still doing here?

32:58.498 --> 32:59.673
I can finish up.

32:59.716 --> 33:01.196
- I'm just killing time
before the play.

33:01.240 --> 33:04.591
- Oh, well, in that case.

33:04.634 --> 33:06.027
- Oh, hi, Miss McGee.

33:06.071 --> 33:08.029
Barbara, Leonard Daniels'
fiancée.

33:08.073 --> 33:09.378
We met at the game.
Hi, again.

33:09.422 --> 33:11.032
- Hello, dear.
- Don't mind me.

33:11.076 --> 33:12.512
I just picked up
our wedding invitations.

33:12.555 --> 33:13.730
Couldn't wait to give them out.

33:13.774 --> 33:15.602
- Oh.
- [giggles]

33:15.645 --> 33:17.996
- I'm sure it's going
to be a beautiful affair.

33:18.039 --> 33:19.301
- [giggles]

33:22.087 --> 33:23.392
- I'm just going to pop in
on Leonard.

33:23.436 --> 33:24.959
That man works himself
to the bone.

33:25.003 --> 33:28.963
[giggles]
Ah, what are you doing?

33:29.007 --> 33:32.053
- Barbara.
[laughter and chatter]

33:32.097 --> 33:33.663
What a surprise.
- It's so nice to see you.

33:33.707 --> 33:35.361
Everything's so nice!

33:35.404 --> 33:37.015
[indistinct chatter]

33:37.058 --> 33:40.757
- Olivia,
I know you're disappointed.

33:40.801 --> 33:45.197
It must feel very unfair to see
Jane place as the runner-up,

33:45.240 --> 33:48.548
but I hope this can serve
as a reminder to us both

33:48.591 --> 33:50.071
that there are some situations

33:50.115 --> 33:53.248
where a woman doesn't have
to settle for second place.

33:53.292 --> 33:59.428
♪

34:03.954 --> 34:07.045
- [sighs]
Thanks, Miss McGee.

34:07.088 --> 34:08.871
I'll get on these.

34:08.916 --> 34:12.440
♪

34:12.485 --> 34:15.574
[suspenseful music]

34:15.618 --> 34:22.755
♪

34:23.235 --> 34:25.933
[hair sizzles]
- ♪ Mi, mi, mi, mi, mi ♪

34:25.976 --> 34:27.978
- [sputtering]

34:28.022 --> 34:31.112
Oh!
- ♪ Mi, mi, mi, mi, mi

34:31.156 --> 34:32.983
- Ooh, my stomach hurts.

34:33.027 --> 34:35.072
I'm ready
for this all to be over.

34:35.116 --> 34:36.335
- Amen.

34:36.378 --> 34:39.206
- Leads shouldn't complain.
It's tacky.

34:39.251 --> 34:43.255
- ♪ Mi, mi, mi, mi, mi

34:45.387 --> 34:48.172
- [scoffs]
If you put any more of that on,

34:48.216 --> 34:50.130
you're going to look
like a thumb onstage.

34:51.306 --> 34:53.178
[scoffs]
Let me help you.

34:53.221 --> 34:55.092
- I'm good.
- Here, it's fine.

34:55.136 --> 34:58.531
- I got it!
[room goes silent]

35:05.059 --> 35:06.321
[door slams]

35:06.365 --> 35:09.368
[indistinct chatter]
- Okay, back to business.

35:12.806 --> 35:13.807
- Leave me alone!

35:13.850 --> 35:14.938
I just need a minute
to prepare.

35:14.982 --> 35:17.332
[sighs heavily]

35:19.987 --> 35:21.945
- Your hair is brown.

35:21.989 --> 35:23.512
- Not this again.

35:25.384 --> 35:28.038
- Your hair is brown.

35:28.082 --> 35:29.736
- I gotta to get dressed.

35:32.086 --> 35:34.219
- Your hair is brown.

35:34.262 --> 35:36.221
- [sighs]

35:36.264 --> 35:38.788
My hair is brown.

35:40.790 --> 35:42.401
- Your hair is brown.

35:44.968 --> 35:46.840
- My hair is brown.

35:49.234 --> 35:50.713
- You're scared.

35:54.891 --> 35:56.763
- I'm scared.

35:56.806 --> 35:59.722
[takes deep breath]

35:59.766 --> 36:01.333
- [sighs]

36:01.376 --> 36:04.597
[soft dramatic music]

36:04.640 --> 36:07.077
- You're scared.

36:07.121 --> 36:09.732
- I'm scared.

36:09.776 --> 36:11.212
- You're scared.

36:11.256 --> 36:12.822
- I'm scared.

36:12.866 --> 36:14.607
- I'm scared.

36:14.650 --> 36:15.956
♪

36:15.999 --> 36:19.089
- Your hair is brown.

36:19.133 --> 36:21.701
- My hair is brown.

36:21.744 --> 36:28.664
♪

36:34.104 --> 36:37.195
[nervous giggling]

36:39.414 --> 36:41.111
- [chuckles softly]

36:41.155 --> 36:44.245
♪

36:44.289 --> 36:47.857
[soft tense music]

36:47.901 --> 36:52.253
[door opens and closes]

36:52.297 --> 36:54.560
♪

36:55.691 --> 36:57.389
- These costumes
are really something.

36:57.432 --> 37:00.696
- Mm-hmm.
- I thought you were on props.

37:00.740 --> 37:03.264
- I'm learning to step out
of my comfort zone.

37:07.050 --> 37:09.401
Hey, you okay?

37:09.444 --> 37:11.359
- Uh--
- Where is Cynthia?

37:11.403 --> 37:12.969
Has anyone seen her?

37:13.013 --> 37:15.842
- [scoffs] If she's gonna be
a diva and hold up the curtain,

37:15.885 --> 37:17.365
I will be impressed.

37:17.409 --> 37:18.888
- I'm sure she's still
in the dressing room.

37:21.239 --> 37:23.980
- Costumes assistance, please.

37:27.941 --> 37:29.029
- Break a leg.

37:29.072 --> 37:31.988
[soft dramatic music]

37:32.032 --> 37:33.512
♪

37:33.555 --> 37:35.949
- Places, everyone!
Places!

37:35.992 --> 37:38.299
- [exhales deeply]

37:38.343 --> 37:40.649
♪

37:40.693 --> 37:42.303
- Where else could she be?

37:42.347 --> 37:45.480
- Nancy?

37:45.524 --> 37:49.310
[tense music]

37:49.354 --> 37:52.313
- Okay.
Something's very wrong.

37:52.357 --> 37:54.359
I have to find Cynthia.
- [sighs]

37:54.402 --> 37:57.100
- But first...

37:57.144 --> 37:58.319
strip.

37:58.363 --> 37:59.842
- What?

37:59.886 --> 38:01.235
- Strip.
Hurry up.

38:01.279 --> 38:02.323
- Nancy, you can't mean--

38:02.367 --> 38:03.803
- Are we really
going to do this?

38:03.846 --> 38:06.545
Come on, Hazel.
You know all the lines.

38:06.588 --> 38:08.416
You're basically
the same dress size.

38:08.460 --> 38:10.375
You should have been Juliet
the whole time.

38:10.418 --> 38:12.115
This is the only way
to save the show,

38:12.159 --> 38:15.249
et cetera, et cetera.

38:15.293 --> 38:16.816
[soft upbeat music]

38:16.859 --> 38:18.339
- Well, I suppose it does make
the most logical sense

38:18.383 --> 38:19.340
for me to step in.

38:19.384 --> 38:21.386
- So glad we got there.

38:21.429 --> 38:24.040
Strip.
- Okay.

38:24.084 --> 38:25.433
- Come on, come on, come on!
- Okay!

38:25.477 --> 38:27.435
- Faster, faster, faster.
- Okay, okay!

38:27.479 --> 38:30.395
[soft downbeat music]

38:30.438 --> 38:37.619
♪

38:47.325 --> 38:49.327
[door opens]

38:49.370 --> 38:50.415
- Olivia.
- [gasps]

38:50.458 --> 38:51.459
- I'm so glad I found you.

38:51.503 --> 38:53.809
I just had the craziest day.

38:53.853 --> 38:56.725
- It looks like it.
What happened?

38:56.769 --> 39:00.120
- Susan, of all people,
just made me realize

39:00.163 --> 39:02.340
that I don't want to play
second fiddle to Buddy.

39:02.383 --> 39:04.342
- Susan.
Interesting.

39:04.385 --> 39:05.430
- Forget the source.

39:05.473 --> 39:07.475
The point is that
the Pink Ladies

39:07.519 --> 39:09.695
have power at the school.

39:11.044 --> 39:13.438
- More than you think.
Look at this.

39:13.481 --> 39:15.875
The vote counts,
they don't match up.

39:15.918 --> 39:17.311
I don't think
I have enough evidence

39:17.355 --> 39:18.530
to prove anything, but--

39:18.573 --> 39:20.227
- Maybe it doesn't matter.

39:20.270 --> 39:24.274
I don't have to be president
for us to make a difference.

39:24.318 --> 39:28.191
I-I don't want to do any
of it without the Pink Ladies.

39:28.235 --> 39:30.629
- That's good to hear.

39:32.108 --> 39:34.720
- Also...

39:34.763 --> 39:38.071
I have something else
to tell you.

39:38.114 --> 39:39.638
I kissed Buddy.

39:39.681 --> 39:41.161
And it was after
I broke things off with Richie,

39:41.204 --> 39:42.945
who I know you didn't want me
to date anyways,

39:42.989 --> 39:44.512
but it's probably still weird
because he's your brother

39:44.556 --> 39:45.818
and I don't know how
to feel about any of it

39:45.861 --> 39:46.993
and I'm sorry
I didn't tell you.

39:47.036 --> 39:49.256
You probably think
I'm such an idiot.

39:49.299 --> 39:50.692
[sighs]

39:50.736 --> 39:54.566
- [sighs]
It's okay.

39:54.609 --> 39:57.438
Those things are complicated.

39:57.482 --> 40:00.441
[inhales deeply]
I was about to go

40:00.485 --> 40:03.139
meet with Mr. Daniels.

40:03.183 --> 40:06.360
In his office.

40:06.404 --> 40:08.580
- Oh.

40:08.623 --> 40:10.538
That sounds complicated too.

40:10.582 --> 40:14.499
- Yeah, it is.

40:14.542 --> 40:17.676
But I've decided that
I'm not going to.

40:17.719 --> 40:19.895
I'm not going to be
second place either.

40:19.939 --> 40:21.984
[footsteps approaching]
- [giggles] Nancy.

40:22.028 --> 40:24.291
What's wrong?
- We have to go.

40:24.334 --> 40:26.249
It's Cynthia.

40:26.293 --> 40:27.294
- Cynthia.

40:27.337 --> 40:30.297
[suspenseful music]

40:30.340 --> 40:32.255
♪

40:32.299 --> 40:35.215
[applause]

40:47.314 --> 40:49.359
- Where is this girl?

40:49.403 --> 40:51.884
What Juliet?

40:51.927 --> 40:54.147
[light switch echoing]

40:57.455 --> 41:00.066
[crowd whispering]

41:02.677 --> 41:05.114
What Juliet?

41:05.158 --> 41:08.378
[heart pounding]

41:08.422 --> 41:11.381
- [breathing shakily]

41:11.425 --> 41:14.384
[soft suspenseful music]

41:14.428 --> 41:16.517
♪

41:16.561 --> 41:19.302
[crowd murmuring]

41:19.346 --> 41:22.958
♪

41:23.002 --> 41:26.614
♪ Is this really happening?

41:26.658 --> 41:30.531
♪ And not inside a dream?

41:30.575 --> 41:33.447
♪ The opposite of fantasy

41:33.491 --> 41:38.408
♪ It's real, I'm here, I'm me

41:38.452 --> 41:43.805
♪ I'm shaking off shadows,
a key on a kite ♪

41:43.849 --> 41:50.812
♪ I'm finding my light

41:50.856 --> 41:53.989
[soft upbeat music]

41:54.033 --> 41:55.643
♪

41:55.687 --> 41:59.560
♪ The safety of invisible

41:59.604 --> 42:03.216
♪ Had its arms 'round me

42:03.259 --> 42:05.914
♪ Shining bright is difficult

42:05.958 --> 42:10.876
♪ It's scary when you're seen

42:10.919 --> 42:16.446
♪ I'm shaking off shadows,
a key on a kite ♪

42:16.490 --> 42:22.452
♪ I'm finding my light

42:22.496 --> 42:25.325
♪

42:25.368 --> 42:28.763
♪ Sure, I still might
be afraid ♪

42:28.807 --> 42:32.680
♪ But at least
I'm standing here ♪

42:32.724 --> 42:35.857
♪ Until it's muscle memory

42:35.901 --> 42:40.166
♪ I will lean into the dare

42:40.209 --> 42:44.997
♪ I'll lean into the dare

42:46.868 --> 42:49.784
[all gasping]

42:49.828 --> 42:53.527
♪

42:53.571 --> 42:57.009
♪ This is really happening

42:57.052 --> 43:00.839
♪ If consequences come

43:00.882 --> 43:03.406
♪ At least
I felt this side of me ♪

43:03.450 --> 43:08.760
♪ I've
lived, I've lived because ♪

43:08.803 --> 43:14.156
♪ I'm shaking off shadows,
a key on a kite ♪

43:14.200 --> 43:17.986
♪ I'm finding my,
I'm finding my ♪

43:18.030 --> 43:19.858
♪ I'm finding my

43:19.901 --> 43:25.820
♪ I'm finding my light

43:25.864 --> 43:30.042
♪ I'm finding my,
I'm finding my ♪

43:30.085 --> 43:34.437
♪ I'm finding my

43:34.481 --> 43:35.961
♪ Light

43:42.837 --> 43:44.709
[locks unlatching]

43:48.103 --> 43:49.191
- Nope!

43:50.715 --> 43:52.194
- We're worried about you.

43:52.238 --> 43:53.195
What happened?

43:55.154 --> 43:57.460
- I don't want
to talk about it.

43:57.504 --> 44:00.899
I'm serious! I-I really
don't want to talk about it.

44:00.942 --> 44:03.684
- So let's not talk about it.

44:03.728 --> 44:05.207
- I would love
to not talk about it.

44:05.251 --> 44:07.122
- I can't wait
to not talk about it.

44:07.166 --> 44:09.385
All we ever do
is talk about elections

44:09.429 --> 44:11.300
and plans and schemes.

44:11.344 --> 44:12.475
I'm exhausted.

44:12.519 --> 44:14.042
- Me too.
- [groans]

44:16.958 --> 44:19.874
- So what are we
gonna do instead?

44:19.918 --> 44:20.962
- Can we just watch TV?

44:21.006 --> 44:22.616
- [gasps] Yes!
- Television!

44:22.660 --> 44:24.662
I love television.

44:24.705 --> 44:26.620
[TV static hissing]

44:26.664 --> 44:29.754
[applause]

44:30.668 --> 44:32.582
[laughter]

44:32.626 --> 44:35.542
[soft upbeat music]

44:35.585 --> 44:42.244
♪

44:42.288 --> 44:46.945
- For never was a story
of more woe than this,

44:46.988 --> 44:50.078
of Juliet and her Romeo.

44:54.474 --> 44:55.910
[slow upbeat music]

44:55.954 --> 44:58.696
[cheers and applause]

44:58.739 --> 45:05.746
♪

45:14.146 --> 45:16.757
[cheers and applause
get louder]

45:16.801 --> 45:18.454
♪

45:18.498 --> 45:23.111
- No more plaid for Hazel.
[chuckles]

45:23.155 --> 45:26.724
- "Hazelle," you were the show.

45:26.767 --> 45:29.596
- Thank you, Mr. Vaughan.

